properties.headline: Winter Storm Watch issued January 8 at 3:10PM PST until January 11 at 4:00AM PST by NWS Seattle WA
properties.description:
* WHAT...Heavy snow possible. Total snow accumulations of 12 to 24
inches possible.

* WHERE...Cascade mountains and valleys of Whatcom and Skagit
Counties, including Maple Falls, the Mount Baker Ski Area,
Newhalem, Lyman, and Concrete, Cascade mountains and valleys of
Snohomish and King Counties, including Darrington, Index,
Skykomish, Stevens Pass, and Snoqualmie Pass and Cascade
mountains and valleys of Pierce and Lewis Counties, including
the Crystal Mountain Ski Area, Paradise on Mount Rainier.

* WHEN...From early Friday morning through late Friday night.

* IMPACTS...Travel could be very difficult to impossible.
properties.instruction: Monitor the latest forecasts for updates on this situation.

NWSheadline: WINTER STORM WATCH IN EFFECT FROM EARLY FRIDAY MORNING THROUGH LATE FRIDAY NIGHT
